 occasionally broken along the stairs with a few more doors. Storage, and a couple of guest rooms. But still relatively barren, and dusty from lack of occupants. Further down, beneath an old carpet, there was a hidden door to the cellar - which was ominous in feel from the lack of anything down there and no light. The entire place was just so... empty.<br/><br/>She shut the cellar door and brought her eyes to the front door. The latch wasn't set - it was unlocked. This place was truly abandoned. Her steps brought her near, and a hand extended to grasp at the bolt latch. She took a breath, and pushed it into place to lock the door - the sound of that metal hitting in place echoing up the empty tower. It felt like a revelation of sorts - she had come in and locked the place down. Did... this make it <i>her</i> tower now? It certainly felt like it. If the place had been clean she would have assumed there were people that lived here... but it was quite the opposite.<br/><br/>Zera turned in place and tilted her head, looking up the vacant tower once more. This place had much potential to be a dwelling. Her mind started to piece together how she could shape it... what she might build into the foundation. This entryway could make for a cozy entrance, perhaps a small kitchen. Closest storage for food. The landing above - <i>a study. </i>Maybe even... cut out the wall to the platform for an archway - a proper balcony.<br/><br/>She had to laugh and shake her head, clear her thoughts. She was becoming giddy with all the possibilities. In her absolute delight her wings came out and flapped hard to carry her the distance to the top of the spiraling stairs, where she rushed the landing room and the door - unlocking it quickly. Outside, she darted across the platform and let her wings stretch out high and as far as they could go. She ignored the rain that had started to fall, far too elated to care. With a ring of laughter she began to spin and sway into dance. It was an odd sensation she couldn't quite control - a place to build into her own made her absolutely ecstatic. It was a sense of purpose, if only for now. She would follow through on it.<br/></br></font>"}, "post-44934": {"user": null, "user_num": null, "timestamp": "1469216609000", "message": "She hadn't expected to come to this new home with anything. After all, she didn't have a coin to her name. But the mystic gaze of the carved wooden owl was a delightful one, and upon approaching the door on the ground floor she settled it near - letting it stare out endlessly along the walkway. Stepping back she admired how it looked - almost adorable.She had hoped that Ranith & Ryzith Fletcher  were in tow, if the sister had been found of course. But she also understood if the pair had other things to attend to. If they were there, she would turn to glance at them - wondering what their thoughts were upon seeing this lonely spire within the city.", "link_list": ["/user/1258"], "image_list": [], "html": "<font face=\"georgia\">She hadn't expected to come to this new home with anything. After all, she didn't have a coin to her name. But the mystic gaze of the carved wooden owl was a delightful one, and upon approaching the door on the ground floor she settled it near - letting it stare out endlessly along the walkway. Stepping back she admired how it looked - almost adorable.<br><br/>She had hoped that <span itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\"><a class=\"user-link js-user-link user-1258 group-0\" href=\"/user/1258\" itemprop=\"url\" title=\"@ranithryzith\"><span itemprop=\"name\">Ranith &amp; Ryzith Fletcher</span></a></span>  were in tow, if the sister had been found of course. But she also understood if the pair had other things to attend to. If they were there, she would turn to glance at them - wondering what their thoughts were upon seeing this lonely spire within the city.</br></font>"}, "post-44935": {"user": "Ranith & Ryzith Fletcher", "user_num": 1258, "timestamp": "1